unbecoming gowns, and fussy aprons that did not fit. 
Everything was good, well made, and little worn; but Amy‚Äôs 
artistic eyes were much afflicted, especially this winter, 
when her school dress was a dull purple, with yellow dots, 
and no trimming. 

‚ÄúMy only comfort,‚Äù she said to Meg, with tears in her eyes, 
‚Äúis, that mother don‚Äôt take tucks in my dresses whenever I‚Äôm 
naughty, as Maria Parks‚Äô mother does. My dear, it‚Äôs really 
