talked away about great singers whom he had seen, fine 
organs he had heard, and told such charming anecdotes 
that Beth found it impossible to stay in her distant corner, 
but crept nearer and nearer, as if fascinated. At the back of 
his chair she stopped, and stood listening, with her great 


