dress her hair, and Annie to tie her sash, and Belle, the 
engaged sister, praised her white arms; but in their kindness 
Meg saw only pity for her poverty, and her heart felt very 
heavy as she stood by herself, while the others laughed, 


chattered, and flew about like gauzy butterflies. The hard, 
bitter feeling was getting pretty bad, when the maid brought 
