One from her mother made her cheeks glow and her eyes 
fill, for it said to her‚Äî 


‚ÄúMy DEAR: 
‚Äú| write a little word to tell you with how much 
satisfaction | watch your efforts to control your 
temper. You say nothing about your trials, failures, 
or successes, and think, perhaps, that no one sees 
them but the Friend whose help you daily ask, if | 
may trust the well-worn cover of your guidebook. /, 
too, have seen them all, and heartily believe in the 
sincerity of your resolution, since it begins to bear 
fruit. Go on, dear, patiently and bravely, and 
always believe that no one sympathizes more 
tenderly with you than your loving 

‚ÄúMOTHER.‚Äù 


‚ÄúThat does me good! that‚Äôs worth millions of money and 
