‚ÄúYou impertinent boy! of course I‚Äôm not,‚Äù exclaimed Sallie, 
with an air that proved the contrary. 

‚ÄúWhat do you hate most?‚Äù asked Fred. 

‚ÄúSpiders and rice-pudding.‚Äù 

‚ÄúWhat do you like best?‚Äù asked Jo. 

‚ÄúDancing and French gloves.‚Äù 

‚ÄúWell, /think Truth is a very silly play; let‚Äôs have a sensible 
game of Authors, to refresh our minds,‚Äù proposed Jo. 

Ned, Frank, and the little girls joined in this, and, while it 
