‚ÄúPII read a bit to encourage you;‚Äù and Miss Kate read one 
of the most beautiful passages, in a perfectly correct but 


perfectly expressionless manner. 

Mr. Brooke made no comment, as she returned the book to 
Meg, who said innocently‚Äî 

‚Äú| thought it was poetry.‚Äù 

‚ÄúSome of it is. Try this passage.‚Äù 

There was a queer smile about Mr. Brooke‚Äôs mouth as he 
