remembering the Moffat party and the talk after it. 

Ned was offended, and turned to Sallie for consolation, 
saying to her rather pettishly, ‚ÄúThere isn‚Äôt a bit of flirt in that 
girl, is there?‚Äù 

‚ÄúNot a particle; but she‚Äôs a dear,‚Äù returned Sallie, 
defending her friend even while confessing her 
shortcomings. 

‚ÄúShe‚Äôs not a stricken deer, anyway,‚Äù said Ned, trying to be 
witty, and succeeding as well as very young gentlemen 
usually do. 

On the lawn, where it had gathered, the little party 
