‚ÄúAnd hairpins,‚Äù added Laurie, throwing half a dozen into 
Jo‚Äôs lap. ‚ÄúThey grow on this road, Meg; so do combs and 


brown straw hats.‚Äù 

‚ÄúYou have been running, Jo; how could you? When will you 
stop such romping ways?‚Äù said Meg reprovingly, as she 
settled her cuffs, and smoothed her hair, with which the 
wind had taken liberties. 

‚ÄúNever till I‚Äôm stiff and old, and have to use a crutch. Don‚Äôt 
try to make me grow up before my time, Meg: it‚Äôs hard 
