‚ÄúI'll try not to be vain,‚Äù said Amy. ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt think | like it only 
because it‚Äôs so pretty; but | want to wear it as the girl in the 
story wore her bracelet, to remind me of something.‚Äù 

‚ÄúDo you mean Aunt March?‚Äù asked her mother, laughing. 

‚ÄúNo, to remind me not to be selfish.‚Äù Amy looked so 
earnest and sincere about it, that her mother stopped 
laughing, and listened respectfully to the little plan. 


‚ÄúI‚Äôve thought a great deal lately about my ‚Äòbundle of 
naughties,‚Äô and being selfish is the largest one in it; so I‚Äôm 
going to try hard to cure it, if | can. Beth isn‚Äôt selfish, and 
that‚Äôs the reason everyone loves her and feels so bad at the 
