‚ÄúThat‚Äôs a housewifely taste which | am glad to see. | had a 
young friend who set up housekeeping with six sheets, but 
she had finger bowls for company, and that satisfied her,‚Äù 
said Mrs. March, patting the damask tablecloths, with a truly 
feminine appreciation of their fineness. 

‚ÄúI haven‚Äôt a single finger-bowl, but this is a ‚Äòset out‚Äô that 
will last me all my days, Hannah says;‚Äù and Meg looked 
quite contented, as well she might. 

‚ÄúToodles is coming,‚Äù cried Jo from below; and they all went 
down to meet Laurie, whose weekly visit was an important 
event in their quiet lives. 

A tall, broad-shouldered young fellow, with a cropped 
head, a felt-basin of a hat, and a flyaway coat, came 
