and spoil our plans.‚Äù 

‚ÄúNot a prank.‚Äù 

‚ÄúAnd don‚Äôt say funny things when we ought to be sober.‚Äù 

‚Äú| never do; you are the one for that.‚Äù 

‚ÄúAnd | implore you not to look at me during the ceremony; 
| shall certainly laugh if you do.‚Äù 

‚ÄúYou won't see me; you'll be crying so hard that the thick 
fog round you will obscure the prospect.‚Äù 

‚Äú| never cry unless for some great affliction.‚Äù 

‚ÄúSuch as fellows going to college, hey?‚Äù cut in Laurie, with 
