‚ÄúMost remarkable children | ever saw. Which is which?‚Äù 
and Laurie bent like a well-sweep to examine the prodigies. 

‚ÄúAmy put a blue ribbon on the boy and a pink on the girl, 
French fashion, so you can always tell. Besides, one has blue 
eyes and one brown. Kiss them, Uncle Teddy,‚Äù said wicked 
Jo. 

‚ÄúI'm afraid they mightn‚Äôt like it,‚Äù began Laurie, with 
unusual timidity in such matters. 

‚ÄúOf course they will; they are used to it now. Do it this 
minute, sir!‚Äù commanded Jo, fearing he might propose a 
