Mercifully unconscious of what she had done, Jo sat with 
her nose in the air, and a revolutionary aspect which was 
anything but inviting. 

‚ÄúDo you speak French, dear?‚Äù asked Mrs. Carrol, laying her 
hand on Amy‚Äôs. 

‚ÄúPretty well, thanks to Aunt March, who lets Esther talk to 
me as often as | like,‚Äù replied Amy, with a grateful look, 
which caused the old lady to smile affably. 

‚ÄúHow are you about languages?‚Äù asked Mrs. Carrol of Jo. 

‚ÄúDon‚Äôt know a word; I‚Äôm very stupid about studying 
anything; can‚Äôt bear French, it‚Äôs such a slippery, silly sort of 
