‚ÄúGood girl! You deserve to go, and I‚Äôm sure you will some 
day,‚Äù said Aunt March, with an approving pat on the head, 
as Amy picked up her ball for her. 


‚ÄúCrosspatch, draw the latch, 
Sit by the fire and spin,‚Äù 


squalled Polly, bending down from his perch on the back of 
her chair to peep into Jo‚Äôs face, with such a comical air of 
impertinent inquiry that it was impossible to help laughing. 

‚ÄúMost observing bird,‚Äù said the old lady. 

‚ÄúCome and take a walk, my dear?‚Äù cried Polly, hopping 
