the valleys, with deer feeding in the parks. It was 
early in the morning, but | didn‚Äôt regret getting up 
to see it, for the bay was full of little boats, the 
shore so picturesque, and a rosy sky overhead. | 
never shall forget it. 

‚ÄúAt Queenstown one of my new acquaintances 
left us‚ÄîMr. Lennox‚Äîand when | said something 
about the Lakes of Killarney, he sighed and sung, 
with a look at me‚Äî 


‚ÄòOh, have you e‚Äôer heard of Kate 
Kearney? 

She lives on the banks of Killarney; 

From the glance of her eye, 

Shun danger and fly, 

For fatal‚Äôs the glance of Kate Kearney.‚Äô 


‚ÄúWasn't that nonsensical? 

‚ÄúWe only stopped at Liverpool a few hours. It‚Äôs a 
