XXXII 


TENDER TROUBLES 


‚ÄúJo, I‚Äôm anxious about Beth.‚Äù 

‚ÄúWhy, mother, she has seemed unusually well since the 
babies came.‚Äù 

‚ÄúIt‚Äôs not her health that troubles me now; it‚Äôs her spirits. 
I‚Äôm sure there is something on her mind, and | want you to 
