always open to you, and your own shall be as 
comfortable as | can make it. There are some 
pleasant people in the house if you feel sociable, 
and your evenings are always free. Come to me if 
anything goes wrong, and be as happy as you can. 
There‚Äôs the tea-bell; | must run and change my 
