bad, so | won‚Äôt be worried;‚Äù and taking up her book, she 
said, with a studious face‚Äî 

‚ÄúShall we go on, sir? l'Il be very good and proper now.‚Äù 

‚Äú| shall hope so,‚Äù was all he said, but he meant more than 
she imagined; and the grave, kind look he gave her made 
