and Jo corked up her inkstand, and said, in a fit of very 
wholesome humility‚Äî 

‚ÄúI don‚Äôt know anything; l'Il wait till | do before | try again, 
and, meantime, ‚ÄòSweep mud in the street,‚Äô if | can‚Äôt do 
better; that‚Äôs honest, at least;‚Äù which decision proved that 
her second tumble down the beanstalk had done her some 
