as effective as a well-placed statue. 

‚ÄúGood evening, Diana!‚Äù said Laurie, with the look of 
satisfaction she liked to see in his eyes when they rested on 
her. 

‚ÄúGood evening, Apollo!‚Äù she answered, smiling back at 
him, for he, too, looked unusually debonair, and the thought 
