Daisy‚Äôs bib, with an injured air. 

‚ÄúGoes on how, my dear?‚Äù asked her mother anxiously. 

‚ÄúHe‚Äôs away all day, and at night, when I want to see him, 
he is continually going over to the Scotts‚Äô. It isn‚Äôt fair that | 
should have the hardest work, and never any amusement. 
Men are very selfish, even the best of them.‚Äù 

‚ÄúSo are women; don‚Äôt blame John till you see where you 
