‚Äúthat boy,‚Äù and in a minute she began again. 

‚ÄúWhat are you doing just now?‚Äù 

‚ÄúWatching lizards.‚Äù 

‚ÄúNo, no; | mean what do you intend and wish to do?‚Äù 

‚ÄúSmoke a cigarette, if you'll allow me.‚Äù 

‚ÄúHow provoking you are! | don‚Äôt approve of cigars, and | 
will only allow it on condition that you let me put you into 
my sketch; | need a figure.‚Äù 

‚ÄúWith all the pleasure in life. How will you have me‚Äîfull- 
length or three-quarters, on my head or my heels? | should 
respectfully suggest a recumbent posture, then put yourself 
in also, and call it ‚ÄòDolce far niente‚Äô?‚Äù 

‚ÄúStay as you are, and go to sleep if you like. /intend to 
work hard,‚Äù said Amy, in her most energetic tone. 

‚ÄúWhat delightful enthusiasm!‚Äù and he leaned against a 
tall urn with an air of entire satisfaction. 

‚ÄúWhat would Jo say if she saw you now?‚Äù asked Amy 
impatiently, hoping to stir him up by the mention of her still 
more energetic sister‚Äôs name. 

‚ÄúAs usual, ‚ÄòGo away, Teddy, I‚Äôm busy!‚Äô‚Äù He laughed as he 
spoke, but the laugh was not natural, and a shade passed 
