‚ÄúNever,‚Äù she answered, with a despondent but decided air. 
‚ÄúRome took all the vanity out of me; for after seeing the 


wonders there, | felt too insignificant to live, and gave up all 
my foolish hopes in despair.‚Äù 

‚ÄúWhy should you, with so much energy and talent?‚Äù 

‚ÄúThat‚Äôs just why‚Äîbecause talent isn‚Äôt genius, and no 
