‚ÄúYou are not engaged, | hope?‚Äù and Laurie looked very 
elder-brotherly and grave all of a sudden. 

‚ÄúNo.‚Äù 


‚ÄúBut you will be, if he comes back and goes properly down 
upon his knees, won't you?‚Äù 

‚ÄúVery likely.‚Äù 

‚ÄúThen you are fond of old Fred?‚Äù 

‚Äú| could be, if | tried.‚Äù 

‚ÄúBut you don‚Äôt intend to try till the proper moment? Bless 
my soul, what unearthly prudence! He‚Äôs a good fellow, Amy, 
