He longed to lay Amy‚Äôs head down on his shoulder, and tell 
her to have a good cry, but he did not dare; so took her hand 
instead, and gave it a sympathetic squeeze that was better 
than words. 


‚ÄúYou needn't say anything; this comforts me,‚Äù she said 
softly. ‚ÄúBeth is well and happy, and | mustn‚Äôt wish her back; 
but | dread the going home, much as | long to see them all. 
We won't talk about it now, for it makes me cry, and I want 
to enjoy you while you stay. You needn‚Äôt go right back, need 
