‚Äú| beg your pardon, | didn‚Äôt see the name distinctly. Never 
mind, | can walk. I‚Äôm used to plodding in the mud,‚Äù returned 
Jo, winking hard, because she would have died rather than 
openly wipe her eyes. 


Mr. Bhaer saw the drops on her cheeks, though she turned 
her head away; the sight seemed to touch him very much, 
for, suddenly stooping down, he asked in a tone that meant 
a great deal‚Äî 

‚ÄúHeart‚Äôs dearest, why do you cry?‚Äù 

Now, if Jo had not been new to this sort of thing she would 
