train and teach in his own way, and father will help him. | 
can feed and nurse and pet and scold them; and mother will 
be my standby. I‚Äôve always longed for lots of boys, and never 
had enough; now | can fill the house full, and revel in the 
little dears to my heart‚Äôs content. Think what luxury‚Äî 
Plumfield my own, and a wilderness of boys to enjoy it with 
