‚ÄúNow don‚Äôt be a wet-blanket, Teddy. Of course I shall have 
rich pupils, also‚Äîperhaps begin with such altogether; then, 
when I‚Äôve got a start, | can take a ragamuffin or two, just for 
a relish. Rich people‚Äôs children often need care and comfort, 
