time they need most patience and kindness. People laugh at 
them, and hustle them about, try to keep them out of sight, 
and expect them to turn, all at once, from pretty children 
into fine young men. They don‚Äôt complain much‚Äîplucky 
little souls‚Äîbut they feel it. I‚Äôve been through something of 
it, and | know all about it. I‚Äôve a special interest in such 
